					Latest Key Developments (Source: Significant Developments)




Hogg Robinson sees FY result in-line with market expectations
Friday, 22 Jul 2016 05:14am EDT 
Hogg Robinson Group Plc : Traded in line with our expectations from April 1 2016 to date . In relation to any EU referendum effect, there has been an initial softening in activity; too early to assess any longer-term impact . Will deliver a full-year performance in-line with market expectations . For three months to June 30, revenue up 2 pct, 3 pct lower at constant currency versus prior year, client travel activity down 3 pct .Says earnings performance is not materially exposed to exchange rate movements. 
			
Full Article





Hogg Robinson Group Plc sees FY 2016 outlook in line with market expectations
Tuesday, 16 Feb 2016 02:00am EST 
Hogg Robinson Group Plc:Says the board continues to believe that the company will deliver a FY 2016 growth performance in line with market expectations. 
			
Full Article





Hogg Robinson Group Plc announces appointment of chairman elect
Thursday, 17 Dec 2015 02:00am EST 
Hogg Robinson Group Plc:Says Nigel Northridge is to be appointed as a Non-Executive Director of the Company and as Chairman elect, with effect from 1 January 2016.Says it is anticipated that Northridge will assume the Chairmanship of the Board with effect from 1 April 2016, at which time John Coombe will retire from the Board. 
			
Full Article





Hogg Robinson Group Plc declares interim dividend
Wednesday, 25 Nov 2015 02:00am EST 
Hogg Robinson Group Plc:Declares interim dividend of 0.68p per share, up 8 pct. on the interim payment a year ago.Says this dividend will be paid on Jan. 4, 2016 to shareholders on register at close of business on Dec. 4, 2015. 
			
Full Article





