Hogg Robinson Group

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search


Hogg Robinson Group





Type

Public


Industry
Corporate services


Headquarters
Basingstoke, UK



Key people

John Coombe, Chairman
David Radcliffe, Chief Executive Officer


Website
HRGFraedom


Hogg Robinson Group is a publicly listed international corporate services organisation with headquarters in the UK. Their brands include Fraedom, a rapidly expanding software company that specialises in expense management and advanced payment technology, HRG, a global travel management company and eWings.com, a travel management company for small to medium sized companies[1]. Hogg Robinson Group wholly acquired Spendvision in 2012,[2][3][4] before rebranding it as Fraedom in 2015.[5]
Hogg Robinson Group was founded in 1845 by brothers-in-law Francis Hogg, a young wine merchant, and Augustus Robinson, an insurance broker. The partnership developed mercantile and insurance interests from offices in Birchin Lane in the City of London.
The company is traded on the London Stock Exchange under the ticker symbol HRG.L.
